addRewardWithPermit(uint256,address,uint.details: Function addReward(...) prevents reentrancy by updating the state before transferring tokens.

params.claimAfterBlocks: The number of blocks after which the reward can be claimed.
params.deadline: The time by which the permit must be used before it expires.
params.isForERC721Stakers: A boolean to indicate if the reward is for ERC721 stakers (true) or ERC20 stakers (false).
params.max: A boolean to indicate if the maximum amount of tokens should be approved (true) or the specified amount (false).
params.poolId: The ID of the pool to which the reward will be added.
params.r: Half of the ECDSA signature pair.
params.rewardAmount: The amount of the reward token to be added.
params.rewardToken: The token that will be used for the reward.
params.s: Half of the ECDSA signature pair.
params.v: The recovery byte of the signature.

returns.rewardId: The ID of the newly added reward in the pool.

calculateReward(address,uint256,uint256).details: This function is an external wrapper around `_calculateReward`,      necessary for try/catch in `getReward`.

params.rewardId: The ID of the reward within the pool.

returns._0: token The ERC20 token in which the reward is denominated.
returns._1: amount The amount of reward the staker is eligible to claim.

claimRewards(uint256[],uint256[][],addre.custom:error: RewardIsEmpty Thrown if the reward amount is zero or has already been claimed.RewardTransferFailed Thrown if the transfer of reward tokens to the recipient fails.RewardIsNotYetAvailableForClaim Thrown if an attempt is made to claim a reward before the specified waiting period has elapsed since the reward's distribution.RewardAlreadyClaimed Thrown if an attempt is made to claim a reward that has already been claimed by the user.RewardNotFoundInPool Thrown if any of the provided reward IDs do not correspond to valid rewards in the specified pools.StakerDoesNotHaveStakesInPool Thrown if the user does not have stakes in one of the specified pools and is therefore ineligible to claim rewards from that pool.
claimRewards(uint256[],uint256[][],addre.details: The function calculates the rewards for the given pools and reward IDs, then transfers the rewards using ERC20Q's cross-chain transfer.

params.chainSelector: The identifier of the target chain for the CCIP cross-chain transfer.
params.poolIds: An array of pool IDs from which the user wants to claim rewards. Each pool ID must correspond to a pool where the user has staked tokens and earned rewards.
params.recipient: The address to receive the claimed rewards. If set to the zero address, the rewards will be sent to the caller's address.
params.rewardIds: A two-dimensional array of reward IDs that the user wants to claim, corresponding to each pool ID in the poolIds array. Each inner array of reward IDs is associated with the pool ID at the same index in the poolIds array.

returns.amounts: A two-dimensional array of uint256 values representing the amounts of each reward token claimed from each pool. The structure mirrors the tokens array.
returns.tokens: A two-dimensional array of IERC20 tokens representing the types of rewards claimed from each pool. Each inner array corresponds to the rewards claimed from the pool at the same index in the poolIds array.

params.rewardId: The ID of the reward within the pool.

returns._0: _ The amount of rewards claimed by the staker for the specified reward in the pool.

params.poolId: The ID of the pool to retrieve information for.

returns.poolDetails: Detailed information about the pool specific to the staker.

params.poolId: The ID of the pool to retrieve.

returns.poolDetails: The details of the specified pool.

params.poolId: The ID of the pool containing the reward.
params.rewardId: The ID of the reward within the pool.

returns.rewardDetails: Detailed information about the reward specific to the staker.

params.poolId: The ID of the pool containing the reward.
params.rewardId: The ID of the reward within the specified pool.

returns.rewardDetails: The details of the specified reward.

returns._0: _ An array of rewards for the specified pool.

params.stakeId: The ID of the specific stake within the pool.

returns._0: _ An array of stakes by the staker in the pool.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

stakeWithPermit(uint256,uint256,uint256,.details: Function stake(...) uses the nonReentrant modifier from OpenZeppelin to prevent reentrancy attacks.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to stake in the pool.
params.deadline: The time by which the permit must be used before it expires. This is typically a timestamp.
params.max: If set to true, the permit will approve the maximum uint256 value, allowing unlimited transfers.            If false, the permit will only approve the specified amount.
params.poolId: The ID of the pool in which to stake tokens.
params.r: Half of the ECDSA signature pair, specifically the first 32 bytes.
params.s: Half of the ECDSA signature pair, specifically the second 32 bytes.
params.v: The recovery byte of the signature, part of the ECDSA signature components.

returns.stakeId: The ID of the newly created stake record.

params.ierc20: The address of the ERC20 token contract. If this is the token type being queried,               `ierc721` should be zero.
params.ierc721: The address of the ERC721 token contract. If this is the token type being queried,                `ierc20` should be zero.
params.user: The address of the user to query the token information for.

returns.token: A `Token` struct containing details about the token such as its address, name,               symbol, decimals, user's balance, and approval status.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addRewardWithPermit(uint256,address,uint.notice: Adds a reward to a pool with a permit, allowing the sender to approve and add a reward in a single transaction.

calculateReward(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculates the reward for a staker in a given pool.

claimRewards(uint256[],uint256[][],addre.notice: Claims rewards from specified pools and distributes them to a recipient address across different chains.

getClaimedAmount(address,uint256,uint256.notice: Retrieves the amount of rewards that have already been claimed         by a staker for a specific reward in a pool.

getPool(address,uint256).notice: Retrieves pool details for a specific staker by pool ID.

getPool(uint256).notice: Retrieves details of a specific pool by its ID.

getReward(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Retrieves reward details for a specific staker in a given pool.

getReward(uint256,uint256).notice: Retrieves details of a specific reward in a pool.

getRewards(uint256).notice: Retrieves rewards associated with a specific pool.

getStake(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Retrieves details of a specific stake a user has in a pool.

getStakes(address,uint256).notice: Fetches stakes for a given staker in a specific pool.

getTotalPools().notice: Retrieves the total number of pools.

stakeWithPermit(uint256,uint256,uint256,.notice: Stakes tokens in a pool with a permit, combining ERC20 token approval and staking in a single transaction.

tokenInfo(address,address,address).notice: Retrieves information about a specific token for a user, including name, symbol,         decimals, balance, and approval status.
